<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="17" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="17">
The abdomen of 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" genus="G." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="G. irradiata" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="irradiata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">G. irradiata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is oval and wider than long. Color of the abdomen is yellowish. The anterior edge of the abdomen is strongly curved backwards. Abdominal sigilla are very small. Abdominal spines are reddish. Anterior spines are shortest. Median spines are longest (
<bibRefCitation author="Walckenaer, CA" journalOrPublisher="Roret, Paris" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" refId="B91" refString="Walckenaer, CA, 1841. Histoire naturelle des Insects. Apteres. Tome deuxieme. Roret, Paris" title="Histoire naturelle des Insects. Apteres. Tome deuxieme." year="1841">Walckenaer 1841</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Merian, P" journalOrPublisher="Zoologische Jahrbuecher, Abteilung fuer Systematik, Geographie und Biologie der Tiere" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" pagination="165 - 354" refId="B57" refString="Merian, P, 1911. Die Spinnenfauna von Celebes. Beitraege zur Tiergeographie im Indoaustralischen Archipel. Zoologische Jahrbuecher, Abteilung fuer Systematik, Geographie und Biologie der Tiere 31: 165 - 354" title="Die Spinnenfauna von Celebes. Beitraege zur Tiergeographie im Indoaustralischen Archipel." volume="31" year="1911">Merian 1911</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Dahl, F" journalOrPublisher="Mitteilungen aus dem Zoologischen Museum in Berlin" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" pagination="235 - 301" refId="B17" refString="Dahl, F, 1914. Die Gasteracanthen des Berliner Zoologischen Museums und deren geographische Verbreitung. Mitteilungen aus dem Zoologischen Museum in Berlin 7: 235 - 301" title="Die Gasteracanthen des Berliner Zoologischen Museums und deren geographische Verbreitung." volume="7" year="1914">Dahl 1914</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="17">
The specimens of 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" genus="G." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="G. irradiata" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="irradiata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">G. irradiata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
collected from Thailand belong to 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Dahl’s">Dahl's</normalizedToken>
collection (
<bibRefCitation author="Dahl, F" journalOrPublisher="Mitteilungen aus dem Zoologischen Museum in Berlin" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" pagination="235 - 301" refId="B17" refString="Dahl, F, 1914. Die Gasteracanthen des Berliner Zoologischen Museums und deren geographische Verbreitung. Mitteilungen aus dem Zoologischen Museum in Berlin 7: 235 - 301" title="Die Gasteracanthen des Berliner Zoologischen Museums und deren geographische Verbreitung." volume="7" year="1914">Dahl 1914</bibRefCitation>
). However, the sampling locality was only noted as 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“Siam.”">&quot;Siam.&quot;</normalizedToken>
Based on its distribution records from previous study, it is possible that 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" genus="G." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="G. irradiata" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="irradiata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">G. irradiata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
might be found in the southern and/or eastern parts of Thailand (
<bibRefCitation author="World Spider Catalog" journalOrPublisher="Biodiversity and Conservation" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" publicationUrl="http://wsc.nmbe.ch" refId="B97" refString="World Spider Catalog, 2020. World Spider Catalog. Version 21.0. Natural History Museum Bern. http://wsc.nmbe.ch" title="World Spider Catalog. Version 21.0. Natural History Museum Bern." url="http://wsc.nmbe.ch" year="2020">World Spider Catalog 2020</bibRefCitation>
). We failed to collect 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" genus="G." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="G. irradiata" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="irradiata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">G. irradiata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in this study.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="17" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Distribution and habitat.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="17">
Vietnam, Thailand, and Indonesia (Sulawesi, Sumatra, Lombok, and Java) (
<bibRefCitation author="Dahl, F" journalOrPublisher="Mitteilungen aus dem Zoologischen Museum in Berlin" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" pagination="235 - 301" refId="B17" refString="Dahl, F, 1914. Die Gasteracanthen des Berliner Zoologischen Museums und deren geographische Verbreitung. Mitteilungen aus dem Zoologischen Museum in Berlin 7: 235 - 301" title="Die Gasteracanthen des Berliner Zoologischen Museums und deren geographische Verbreitung." volume="7" year="1914">Dahl 1914</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="World Spider Catalog" journalOrPublisher="Biodiversity and Conservation" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" publicationUrl="http://wsc.nmbe.ch" refId="B97" refString="World Spider Catalog, 2020. World Spider Catalog. Version 21.0. Natural History Museum Bern. http://wsc.nmbe.ch" title="World Spider Catalog. Version 21.0. Natural History Museum Bern." url="http://wsc.nmbe.ch" year="2020">World Spider Catalog 2020</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
